description: Provision a new ingress endpoint resource.

parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description: A unique token that Amazon SES uses to recognize subsequent retries of the same request. This field is autopopulated if not provided.

parameters.name: IngressPointConfiguration
parameters.description: If you choose an Authenticated ingress endpoint, you must configure either an SMTP password or a secret ARN. SecretArn (string) --- The SecretsManager::Secret ARN of the ingress endpoint resource. SmtpPassword (string) --- The password of the ingress endpoint resource.

nested_params.name: SecretArn
nested_params.description: The SecretsManager::Secret ARN of the ingress endpoint resource.

nested_params.name: SmtpPassword
nested_params.description: The password of the ingress endpoint resource.

parameters.name: IngressPointName
parameters.description: A user friendly name for an ingress endpoint resource.

parameters.name: NetworkConfiguration
parameters.description: Specifies the network configuration for the ingress point. This allows you to create an IPv4-only, Dual-Stack, or PrivateLink type of ingress point. If not specified, the default network type is IPv4-only. PrivateNetworkConfiguration (dict) --- Specifies the network configuration for the private ingress point. The identifier of the VPC endpoint to associate with this private ingress point. PublicNetworkConfiguration (dict) --- Specifies the network configuration for the public ingress point. The IP address type for the public ingress point. Valid values are IPV4 and DUAL_STACK.

nested_params.name: PrivateNetworkConfiguration
nested_params.description: Specifies the network configuration for the private ingress point.

nested_params.name: VpcEndpointId
nested_params.description: The identifier of the VPC endpoint to associate with this private ingress point.

nested_params.name: PublicNetworkConfiguration
nested_params.description: Specifies the network configuration for the public ingress point.

nested_params.name: IpType
nested_params.description: The IP address type for the public ingress point. Valid values are IPV4 and DUAL_STACK.

parameters.name: RuleSetId
parameters.description: The identifier of an existing rule set that you attach to an ingress endpoint resource.

parameters.name: Tags
parameters.description: The tags used to organize, track, or control access for the resource. For example, { 'tags': {'key1':'value1', 'key2':'value2'} }. (dict) --- A key-value pair (the value is optional), that you can define and assign to Amazon Web Services resources. The key of the key-value tag. The value of the key-value tag.

nested_params.description: The key of the key-value tag.

nested_params.name: Value

parameters.description: The identifier of an existing traffic policy that you attach to an ingress endpoint resource.

parameters.description: The type of the ingress endpoint to create.
